Package: claude-desktop-bin
Architecture: amd64
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}, electron | electron-bin | electron33
Recommends: libnotify-bin, sqlite3, qemu-system-x86, ovmf, virtiofsd
Suggests: xdotool, scrot, imagemagick, wmctrl, socat, hyprland, ydotool, grim, jq, kde-spectacle, libglib2.0-bin, python3-gi, gstreamer1.0-pipewire, gnome-screenshot, nodejs
Description: Claude AI Desktop Application
 Claude is an AI assistant created by Anthropic to be helpful,
 harmless, and honest. This desktop application provides native
 access to Claude with features including:
 .
  * Conversational AI assistance
  * Code generation and analysis
  * Document understanding
  * Quick Entry for fast access
  * System tray integration
 .
 Optional dependencies for Computer Use (X11/XWayland sessions):
  * xdotool - Input automation + Quick Entry cursor positioning
  * scrot - Screenshot capture
  * imagemagick - Screenshot fallback (import) and crop (convert)
  * wmctrl - Running app detection
 .
 Optional dependencies for Computer Use (Wayland — wlroots: Sway, Hyprland):
  * ydotool - Input automation (requires ydotoold daemon running)
  * grim - Screenshot capture
  * jq - Window queries on Sway (used with swaymsg)
  * hyprland - Cursor positioning and window queries (Hyprland only)
 .
 Optional dependencies for Computer Use (Wayland — KDE Plasma):
  * ydotool - Input automation (requires ydotoold daemon; v1.0+ needed)
  * xdotool - Cursor position reading and XWayland fallback
  * kde-spectacle - Screenshot capture
  * imagemagick - Multi-monitor screenshot crop (convert)
 .
 Optional dependencies for Computer Use (Wayland — GNOME):
  * ydotool - Input automation (requires ydotoold daemon; v1.0+ needed)
  * xdotool - Cursor position reading and XWayland fallback
  * python3-gi - Portal screenshots on GNOME 46+ (no repeated permission dialogs)
  * gstreamer1.0-pipewire - PipeWire frame capture for portal screenshots
  * libglib2.0-bin - Screenshot capture (gdbus for D-Bus)
  * gnome-screenshot - Screenshot fallback
 .
 Other optional dependencies:
  * socat - Faster Quick Entry toggle via socket (~2ms vs ~25ms python3 — not required)
  * nodejs - For third-party MCP servers requiring system Node.js
 .
 Cowork (agent workspace VM) uses qemu-system-x86, ovmf, and virtiofsd,
 recommended (soft) to match the official Claude Desktop .deb: apt pulls them
 by default but they never block install on minimal/KVM-less hosts. The
 workspace runs in a lightweight KVM VM, so using Cowork additionally needs the
 user in the "kvm" group and the Claude Code CLI installed
 (npm i -g @anthropic-ai/claude-code) — neither of which a package can set up.
 .
 Note: This is an unofficial Linux port of the official Claude
 Desktop application. Requires an Anthropic account to use.
